timeline.bodyText:
If this is going to track whether the writer is closed, then it should make the close idempotent by checking the flag:
  if (!closed) {
    this.closed = true;
    flushRowGroup(true);
    writeStore.close();
    writer.end(metadata);
  }
I would also add a precondition in startRowGroup that checks that closed is false.

